//TABLE 1.42 NCOA File Layout
//FIELD NAME DESCRIPTION FORMAT POSITION
//FILLER Spaces X(19) 1-19
//QM-SEQ-NO Sequential Record Number in NCOA File 9(8) 20-27
//FILLER Spaces X(168) 28-195
//QM-CORRECT-ZIP Correct Zip Code X(5) 196-200
//QM-CORRECT-PLUS4 Correct Zip Code additional 4 digits X(4) 201-204
//FILLER Spaces X(45) 205-249
//QM-COA-FLAG N, M, P, X = Codes from list house file X(1) 250
//QM-COA-SURNAME Last Name X(20) 251-270
//QM-COA-FIRST-NAME First Name X(15) 271-285
//QM-COA-MIDDLE-NAME Middle Name X(15) 286-300
//FILLER Spaces X(20) 301-320
//QM-NEW-STREET1 New Street Address Line 1 X(30) 321-350
//QM-NEW-STREET2 Overflow for Street Address 1 X(10) 351-360
//QM-NEW-CITY City X(15) 361-375
//QM-NEW-STATE State Code X(2) 376-377
//QM-ZIPS Zip plus additional 4-digit zip or Postal Codes X(9) 378-386
//FILLER Spaces X(1) 387
//QM-DELIVER-CODE X = Not a Deliverable Address, no update
//D = Deliverable Address
//G = Box Closed
//K = Moved left no forwarding address
//X(1) 388
//EFFECTIVE-DATE Month and Year X(4) 389-392
//QM-ZIP-INDICATOR (1 or 9)
//1 = last 2 positions of zip code changed
//9 = zip code sectional center changed
//Updates the zip code in Ecometry Retail Enterprise customer
//record
//X(1) 393
//FILLER Spaces X(59) 394-452
//QM-NEW-REF1 Reference line 1 X(30) 453-482
//FILLER Spaces X(7) 483-489
//QM-CUST-NO Customer Number X(10) 490-499
//FILLER Spaces X(11) 500-510
//TOTAL RECORD SIZE = 510 BYTES

